<br>
The virus was spread using a loophole in Microsoft's IIS Software, and could have been prevented if the server was running the most current security patches from windowsupdate.  Once files do get infected, the virus propogates itself into many random files, all the while replicating files with a .eml suffix, until it finally fills up your hard drive with nothing but crap.  And the real kick in the booty is, once a file is infected, it is uncleanable by any antivirus software.  That means all infected files are lost, hope ya got backups.<br>
<br>
FYI, this isn't the first website to get infected either, take a look at MSN.com's news section for a full story on what exactly this virus is capable of. <p>Nuvarre Etienne <Amazon> 
